-- U.S. welcomes Chinese stimulus package: official
-- 
-- Sun Nov 9, 2008 5:56pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/11/09/us-financial-g20-usa-idUSTRE4A83BH20081109

 

 SAO PAULO  (Reuters) - The United States welcomes China's massive government spending package to boost domestic demand and help the Asian giant ride out the financial crisis, a senior U.S. Treasury official said on Sunday. 

 David McCormick, U.S. Treasury Undersecretary for International Affairs, made the remark at a briefing with reporters after a G20 meeting of finance officials and central bankers in Brazil's business capital Sao Paulo. (Reporting by Anna Willard, Writing by Todd Benson)